I'm keeping my eyes on this baby, but why oh why are the thumb buttons arranged front to back instead of top to bottom (MS Sidewinder style)? I may be alone in this, but it just seems more natural for me to flick my thumb up and down than to move it front and back Also, Ben, can you comment on the mouse wheel? Can you flick it left and right? I actually love that feature, made raid healing in WoW a breezeRight now I have an MX Revolution, it's pretty awesome with all the programmable buttons and the dual wheels are fantastic, but it's really not a gaming mouse due to the non replaceable battery (had I known this before buying it I probably wouldn't have ordered it, live and learn) and the mouse tracking stalls some times (although I'm not sure if it's because of the laser, the wireless connection or my dirty old mouse pad )
