quote:Originally posted by MoonShark:quote:Originally posted by Deviation:Right now, the ultimate gaming mouse has got to be the Razer Mamba. Up to 5600 DPI with a 1ms response time on a wireless mouse - that's just crazy. Also $130 MSRP. Do they have a less pricey wired variant (Imperator maybe)? I don't mind a cord (especially if it's the good braided style like on the G5), and while I know batteries have gotten better, but I still don't like them or the associated cost. Although... I'm probably not hardcore enough for another mouse upgrade. Gotta save for a new CPU... It's not the same guts but the shell of the Mamba is essentially the DeathAdder, which still has up to 3500 dpi on a 3G optical sensor. It has a $59.99 MSRP.The most recent wired mouse from Razer, which has the same 5600 DPI 3G laser sensor as the Mamba, is the Imperator, which has a $79.99 MSRP.The Mamba is really a wonderful mouse, however. I hesitated before but now that I've got it, I'm very happy with the purchase.quote:Originally posted by Talden:Re: Owning a good mouse != cheat.Yeah because the 7-10% of us that are left-handed have an excellent selection of hi-spec peripherals...Sigh... Razer makes several ambidextrous mice that are quite comfortable. The Razer Copperhead, my previous mouse, can be found new online for ~$40 and it's still a great mouse and there are plenty of other options.
