quote:Originally posted by YourConscience:quote:Originally posted by MoonShark:[QUOTE]Looks like they swiped a lot of ideas from the Logitech G5, which can only be a good thing for gamers. Though the G5 has FIVE on-the-fly DPS settings My old G5 only had 3 DPI settings; 400, 800, 1600, IIRC.I just bought a Sidewinder a few months ago, and I really dig the vertical thumb buttons. However, this mouse just looks too hilariously awesome for me to discount it completely. I can't wait to see one in person.. the Sidewinder just isn't as comfortable as the G5 it replaced. Then you did not install the Logitech drivers. If you use the standard Windows drivers, you get 3 default settings. If you install the Logitech drivers you can have 5 presets and you can choose the DPI setting for each.
